    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok that makes sense. but i'm worried about the escrow agent specifically. like, who actually holds all that cash? is it just sitting in a bank, or is there some kind of person responsible for making sure nobody touches it until the very end? it feels weird to just have a big chunk of money locked away like that.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The escrow agent, or the title company, is the designated, trusted third party who holds the cash. They aren't just some random person; they are a licensed entity, like a specialized, heavily-supervised clearinghouse for the transaction. Think of them as the gatekeeper, with very strict rules about who can access the funds. They keep it locked up in a secure bank account, but the *responsibility* rests squarely on their shoulders, making sure that money doesn't get misplaced or stolen by any of the other parties.",
